<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 500 Kurds Protest in Paris Against Verdict of Ocalan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- About 500 Kurds demonstrated at the
Place of Concord in Paris Tuesday afternoon in protest of the
verdict of death sentence on Kurdish rebel leader Abdulah Ocalan
by a court in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators included men, women and children, many of
them waving the Kurdish flag and the portrait of Ocalan.
</P>
<P>
A Kurdish demonstration protesting the condemnation of Ocalan
also took place in Marseille.
</P>
<P>
French government has reinforced security in front of Turkish
properties in Paris and other cities.
</P>
<P>
Security has also been reinforced for the Turkish Airlines at
the Orly airport, as well as Air France and two other air
companies flying planes to and from Turkey at the
Roissy-Charles-De-Gaulle airport.
</P>
<P>
The Kurdish Workers Party (PKK) has called on Kurdish people in
Europe to hold ``democratic and political'' demonstrations after
the verdict of Ocalan.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan was convicted of terrorism and separatism and sentenced
to death by a security court of the State of Ankara on the prison
island of Imrali in western Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The death sentence could be reversed by either an appeal court,
or the Turkish Parliament, or Turkish President Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
France has called on the Turkish authorities to reverse the
verdict. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
