<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Welcomes Amnesty Measure by Algerian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- France welcomed on Tuesday the
decision by Algerian President Abdelaziz Bouteflika to pardon
thousands of Islamists and release them from prison.
</P>
<P>
The French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said
that France has always called for a political solution to the
internal conflict of Algeria.
</P>
<P>
``We sincerely hope that the latest initiatives of President
Bouteflika could contribute to an end of the sufferings and
violence in Algeria,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
Bouteflika announced last Friday that he would release
thousands of Islamists from jail on July 5, the Independence Day
of Algeria.
</P>
<P>
He also said that he would organize a national referendum in
September on a ``National Harmony Law,'' which would pardon a
majority of Islamists involved in the conflict with government
since 1992.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 100,000 people have been killed in the conflict
between government forces and Islamists since 1992 in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
On the invitation sent by Boutelika to French President Jacques
Chirac and other French leaders to visit Algeria, the spokeswoman
said that France is ready to increase contacts with Algeria,
including those at political level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
