<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's Former Heads of State to Benefit From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Government decided
on Tuesday to accord certain rights to Romanian former heads of
state.
</P>
<P>
Under the decision, the former heads of state will benefit,
through the duration of their life span, of free protocol houses,
a monthly money allowance equal to that of the president in
charge, a tax-free car, and round-the-clock security service.
</P>
<P>
The right can be accorded at the relative person's request and
will become effective beginning the day when the request is lodged
with the Government. Any deriving expenditure will be borne by the
treasury under a special revenue grossing law.
</P>
<P>
Romania's ex-King Michael I and former President Ion Iliescu
(1990-1996) can be recipients of these rights if they request so.
</P>
</TEXT>
