<HEADLINE> EU Hopes Turkey Not to Execute Ocalan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 29 (Xinhua) - The European Union hoped Turkey
would not execute Kurdish leader Abdullah Ocalan, said a statement
Tuesday in Bonn by the German Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Germany will currently hold the bloc's rotating presidency.
</P>
<P>
And German Interior Minister Otto Schily said also he regretted
the passing of a death sentence against Ocalan and urged Kurd in
Germany to remain calm.
</P>
<P>
Around 100 Kurds chanted slogans in the diplomatic quarter of
Bonn, Germany after a march from a Kurdish cultural centre in the
centre.
</P>
<P>
It said, there are about 500,000 Kurds who live in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan, who is the leader of the Kurdish Workers Party(PKK),
was convicted of treason by a Turkish court on Tuesday and
sentenced to death. 
</P>
