<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, June 29 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO -- A multilateral forum is expected to open next week in
Cairo in a bid to seek ways of reviving the Palestinian-Israeli
peace talks, the Egyptian Gazette newspaper reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian, Jordanian and Israeli delegations will meet in the
three-day event, to be opened by Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa, the English-language paper said.
</P>
<P>
The gathering is expected to send a message to Israeli Prime
Minister-elect Ehud Barak, calling on him to step up efforts aimed
at pushing the peace drive forward, the newspaper said.
(BC-Egypt-Mideast-Peace Forum)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) leader Abdullah
Ocalan was sentenced to death for treason on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Ankara State Security Court gave Ocalan the death
penalty as he "betrayed the country."
</P>
<P>
Ocalan was captured by Turkish special agents in Kenya in
mid-February and detained on Imrali Island in Marmara Sea near
western Turkey's province of Bursa for trials on charges of
treason and separatism. (BC-Turkey-PKK)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz dismissed a
draft resolution by Britain and the Netherlands to the
U.N. Security Council on the Iraqi issue as "dubious."
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Al-Jazeera Satellite Channel Monday
evening, Aziz said the proposal was intended to reforge the
Security Council resolutions in a manner worse than previous
U.N. resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Britain and the Netherlands recently proposed to the Security
Council that the U.N. sanctions on Iraq be suspended after Iraq
fully cooperates with an enlarged body of weapons inspectors,
which will replace the U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM) and carry
out more intrusive inspections on Iraq's banned weapons.
(BC-Iraq-Aziz-Interview)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami said Tuesday that
Iranian-Greek defense talks are not against the interests of any
country, but aimed at establishing security and stability in the
two countries, the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Greek Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos, Khatami expressed regret that in the 20th
century, human beings failed to talk with each other in the
language of culture and logic, but through war, discrimination
and exploitation. (BC-Iran-Greece-Defense Minister)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat Tuesday called on
Israeli Prime Minister-elect Ehud Barak to comply with all
agreements Israel signed with the Palestinians and to stop
settlement activities in the occupied territories.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in Amman after his talks with Jordanian
Prime Minister Abdul Raouf Rawabdeh, Arafat said Israel must
adhere to the Wye River agreement and Oslo accord it reached with
the Palestinians. (BC-Jordan-Palestinians) 
</P>
</TEXT>
