<HEADLINE> LA, Caribbean, EU Sign Action Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Latin American,
Caribbean and European Union countries singed here on Tuesday a
plan of action to promote reforms and expand their relations in
the political, economic, social, cultural and educative fields.
</P>
<P>
The 36 heads of state and of government of 47 countries
attending the first Latin America (LA), the Caribbean and the
European Union (EU) Summit signed Tuesday the documents--
"Priorities for Action" and the "Declaration of Rio."
</P>
<P>
The countries taking part in the summit expressed in the
document their will to promote cooperation in the fields of
infrastructure, entrepreneurial investigation, productive
competitivity, tourism, and alternate energy.
</P>
<P>
According to the document, the countries are willing to
modernize the state structures, with improvements in the electoral
systems and the administration of justice.
</P>
<P>
The plan has decided to intensify cooperation in the fight
against terrorism, organized crime, drug traffic, and to promote
the signing or ratification of the instruments in the matter of
disarming and prohibition of certain weapons.
</P>
<P>
The document names as future actions the promotion of cultural
forums, the diffusion of the cultural heritage, the cooperation in
the zone of audivisual and cinematographical production between
the two regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
