Palestinians, and described his talks with King Abdullah Bin
Hussein and Prime Minister Rawabdeh as "fruitful and
constructive."
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Abdullah and Rawabdeh reiterated Jordan`s
support for all legitimate rights of the Palestinians, including
the establishment of an independent Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah has used many occasions to call on Israeli Prime
Minister-elect Barak to resume peace talks with Arab neighbors
after his May 17 election victory, which brought down the
hard-line Likud government in the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
During Arafat`s visit, Jordan and the Palestinains also
agreed to strengthen bilateral cooperation in efforts to
revive the Middel East peace process, which remained
deadlocked since 1996 when the Likud came to power in Israel.

