<HEADLINE> U.S. Declines Comment on Ocalan Death Sentence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The United States on Tuesday
declined immediate comment on the death sentence imposed on
Kurdish leader Abdullah Ocalan by a Turkish court.
</P>
<P>
"We have long believed that Ocalan is an international
terrorist who should be brought to justice," white House spokesman
Joe Lockhart told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"But there is an automatic appeal here, so the judicial process
is still ongoing (and) so I'm not going to comment on the process
until it's completed," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan was sentenced to death by a Turkish court on Tuesday for
treason over his Kurdstan Workers Party's campaign in Turkey in
which more than 29,000 people have died.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested last year in Kenya by Turkey's agents with the
help from the United States.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the United States warned its citizens of possible
violence once the verdict was handed down.
</P>
<P>
The State Department said in a statement last Wednesday that
U.S. government personnel and facilities around the world were
taking "appropriate" security precautions in case of a violent
reaction to the verdict from Ocalan's supporters. 
</P>
