<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe Tuesday appealed to the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) to speedily approve the release
of the standby balance of payments support for Zimbabwe, saying
Harare urgently needs donor support to revitalize its economy.
</P>
<P>
The macro-economic task force of the Zimbabwean National
Economic Consultative Forum said it is also crucial that other
multilateral and bilateral donors open their doors for Zimbabwe so
that the troubled economy could be turned back to a sustainable
growth path.
</P>
<P>
"We therefore urge the IMF to speedily approve the disbursement
in order to allow other institutions to come to the rescue of
Zimbabwe," said Isaac Takawira, chairman of the macro-economic
task force.
