<HEADLINE> Greece Opposed to Ocalan's Death Sentence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Tuesday voiced its
opposition to Turkey's death sentence handed on Abdullah Ocalan,
leader of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news briefing, Greek government spokesman Yiannis
Nikolaou said his government is opposed to Turkey's decision on
Ocalan, who was arrested by Turkish agents in February.
</P>
<P>
Turkey must show that the way its justice operates is in line
with the practice prevailing in the European Union (EU) countries,
Yiannis Nikolaou said, adding that the Kurdish issue, a Turkish
internal affair, should be resolved through political negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Kurdish National Liberation Front spokesman Roshat Laser
threatened in Athens that Turkey's sentence on Ocalan will lead to
turmoil and instability in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 Kurds staged a demonstration outside the Turkish
Embassy in Athens to show their opposition to the death sentence
on Ocalan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
