<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia Becomes Major Market for Thai Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia has become a major
destination for Thai exports as two-way trade volume in the first
quarter of this year rose to 3.43 billion baht (93 million U.S.
dollars), the Thai Commerce Ministry announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the ministry said that border trade
between the two neighboring countries accounted for 2.67 billion
baht (72 million U.S. dollars) in the first quarter, an increase
of 4.5 percent from the same period of last year, representing
80.2 percent of the overall bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Cambodia has high potential to substitute
the traditional markets that Thailand had relied upon because
consumers of the two countries had similar tastes and needs.
</P>
<P>
Major Thai products exported to Cambodia include food,
construction materials, electrical appliances and autos and parts
while major imports from there include processed wood, livestock,
fish and scrap steel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
