<HEADLINE> Minor Reshuffle in Zambian Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Fredrick Chiluba
has appointed Katele Kalumba, until now Home Affairs Minister to
replace Edith Nawakwi as finance minister, the office of the
president announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Nawakwi, Zambian first female Finance Minister, has been
transferred to the Ministry of Labor and Social Security while
former Labor and Social Security Minister Peter Machungwa has been
moved to the Home Affairs Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Nawakwi was recently been criticized in some financial circles
for her alleged "blunt talking" and is believed to have maintained
lukewarm relations with donors who are backing Zambia's economic
reform program.
</P>
<P>
She was appointed as Zambia's first female cabinet minister in
February 1998, following the dismissal of late Ronald Penza.
</P>
<P>
She had also served as the country's first female Minister of
Agriculture in addition to her term at the Energy and Water
Development Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chiluba appointed Leslie Mbula as Acting Secretary
to the Cabinet pending the retirement of the incumbent Aldridge
Andamson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
