<HEADLINE> Nigerian Bans Belgium Dairy Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has joined the growing list
of countries that have banned the import of dairy products from
Belgium following a food scare connected with the consumption of
these products.
</P>
<P>
Gabriel Osuide, head of the country's Agency for Food and Drugs
 Administration and Control, said here Tuesday that eggs, chicken,
poultry and dairy products were affected in the ban announced
Tuesday. He said the agency's inspectors at the country's
borders had been directed to impound these products while hotels
and supermarkets would be visited to ensure those already in the
country were not sold to the public.
</P>
<P>
Osuide noted that letters had been sent to hotels and
supermarkets requesting them to shun these products and to report
offenders to the agency, the regulatory body for food and drug
control in the west African country. 
</P>
