<HEADLINE> Hundreds of People Escape from Fire in Newfoundland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Almost 1,000 people have been
forced to escape since Monday night from a forest fire in the
central Newfoundland community of Badger.
</P>
<P>
The latest information from Badger said Tuesday that
firefighters have got the upper hand of the forest fire, which,
measuring 10 kilometers by four kilometers at one point, has
destroyed 40 square kilometers of timber.
</P>
<P>
Highways in devastated areas have been reopened to traffic
after fire crews spent much of the night and day spraying water
and foam in the battle against the fire.
</P>
<P>
There has been no report about casualties, but losses caused by
the fire could be millions of Canadian dollars, local reports
said. 
