stayed behind after the withdrawal of regular Serb army and police
forces.
</P>
<P>
"It is not acceptable for the Serbs to remain behind and try to
establish any kind of a presence. So I think KFOR will continue
to look for the Serb presence and insist there be full compliance,
as there should," Cohen said.
</P>
<P>
Cohen and Babiuc discussed Kosovo and other topics, including
Romania's desire to become a NATO member.
</P>
<P>
Cohen said he presented Babiuc with the results of a U.S.
study, done jointly by Cohen's office and the U.S. European
Command, that recommended actions by Romania to strengthen its
case for NATO membership.  
