<HEADLINE> General Assembly to Meet on Population, Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Population and development
catches world attention again when the U.N. General Assembly holds
a special session on the subject from June 30 to July 2.
</P>
<P>
With speakers from over 140 countries, the session will
highlight issues specific to global population and sustainable
development initiatives, such as the mobilization of resources,
adolescent pregnancy, maternal mortality and reproductive health.
</P>
