<HEADLINE> IDB Finances Power Plant in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) on Tuesday announced the closing of 112 million U.S.
dollars in financing for AES Parana for the construction and
operation of a 826 megawatt gas-fired combined cycle generation
plant in San Nicolas, Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The AES Parana power generation project, which has a total cost
of 448 million dollars, includes a 17 kilometer pipeline and a 7
kilometer transmission line that will provide low-cost, reliable
and environmentally clean energy to the national electricity
market, the Washington-based bank said.
</P>
<P>
The financing facility, with a tenor of 12.8 years, consists of
a 60-million-dollar A Loan funded by the IDB from the bank's
ordinary capital and a 52-million-dollar B Loan syndicated to six
commercial financial institutions: ING Barings, Westdeutsche
Landesbank, Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi, KBC Bank NV, Hypo
Vereinsbank and Generale Bank.
</P>
<P>
The project will be co-financed by an export credit facility of
102 million dollars to be provided by the Export-Import Bank of
Japan, commercial financial institutions, and Japan's Ministry of
International Trade and Industry.
</P>
<P>
This is the first infrastructure sector project of the IDB's
Private Sector Department that is co-financed with the Japanese
Export Credit Agency, the IDB said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
