<HEADLINE> Annan Emphasizes Science's Role in Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan said on Tuesday that the International Science Conference
now being held in Budapest "comes at an opportune time".
</P>
<P>
"What better way to mark this symbolic year than to look back
upon a century of remarkable scientific achievements, while
looking forward to a future full of promise as well as
challenges?" he asked in his message to the conference.
</P>
<P>
He said the conference is a call for renewed commitment by the
scientific community to keeping in touch with society and a call
on governments and stake-holders to explore ways of better
supporting science.
</P>
<P>
Emphasizing the role of science as a a catalyst for development,
the U.N. Secretary-general hoped that developing countries will
enhance their capacity to develop their own scientific potential
and create their own tools for development in order to participate
fully in the global economy and to achieve economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The conference from June 26 to July 1 is organized at the
initiative of United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural
Organization (UNESCO) and the International Science Council to
highlight scientists' role in meeting the challenges of teh next
century.  
