<P>
NEW YORK, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose
sharply for a second consecutive session Tuesday a day before
the Federal Reserve would announce its decision on higher
interest rate.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 160.20 at
10,815.35. The blue-chip index rose 102.59 points Monday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was up 20.10 at 1,351.45 and the technology
heavy Nasdaq index was up 39.67 at 2,642.11.
</P>
<P>
The market rallied again today as the Open Market Committee
of the Federal Reserve began a two-day meeting on monetary
policy in Washington. The Federal Reserve was expected to
announce its decision on a rise of 0.25 percent in interest
rates at 2:15 p.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 9.10 at 637.99 and the
American Stock Exchange index rose 3.38 at 777.48. The Russell
2000 index of smaller companies rose 5.47 at 454.08.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,861 up, 1,102 down and 596
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 811.52 million shares from 641.15
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
