<HEADLINE> Pakistan Ready to Talk to India at Any Forum: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is ready to talk with
India at any forum for peaceful solution of all outstanding
disputes, Information Minister Mushahid Hussain said here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We are open to discussion at any forum. India's intransigence
stems from its domestic instability," Mushahid told a news
briefing.
</P>
<P>
The current tension at Kargil on the Line of Control (LoC) is
linked with the larger issue of Kashmir, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the international community to take cognizance of
India's military buildup and the human rights abuse in the
Indian-held Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
"We remain optimistic that there will be a peaceful solution of
the Kashmir problem and the other side will see reason," he said.
</P>
<P>
He dismissed Indian allegations of Pakistan sending
"infiltrators" across LoC. "Pakistan's hands are clean in this
regard," he said.
</P>
<P>
It was the Indian obduracy which had brought the two nuclear
armed neighbors to such heightening tension which could turn into
conflict, said Mushahid.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's basic premise has been discussion and dialogue on
any issue, he said.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question that the United States was calling
for the withdrawal of Pakistani troops from the peaks along LoC,
he said: "It is obviously the misperception or a misunderstanding
of the situation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
