<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1445 GMT, June 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- It is estimated that some 2.5 million children are
compelled to work to earn a living in Indonesia and some 2,000 of
them are known to be employed at high-risk places, Manpower
Minister Fahmi Idris said.
</P>
<P>
Children could work due to economic reasons, but their working
hours should be limited to three hours a day only so that they can
still go to school after work, Antara News Agency Wednesday quoted
Fahmi as saying. (Indonesia-Child Labor)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- A total of 12 rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party (PKK) were killed on Tuesday by the Turkish security forces
in southeastern Turkey, an official statement said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said the Turkish security forces clashed with the PKK in
Havillati Mountain region in Yuksekova town of Hakkari province
bordering Iran. (Turkey-PKK)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- President of the United Nations Economic and Social
Council (ECOSOC) Paolo Fulci has called on the industrialized
countries to involve themselves more in the world's fight against
poverty.
</P>
<P>
"Either we progress together or we sink together," Fulci
warned. "Unless we act swiftly to reverse the spread of abject
poverty, our world tomorrow will be much worse and the prosperity
and security of many will be put at risk."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a UN report said that over 1.5 billion people still
live on less than one U.S. dollar per day and the number of
absolute poor continues to grow.(UN-ECOSOC-Poverty Eradication)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French telecommunications equipment company Alcatel
has obtained a 1.5 billion U.S. dollar contract to build a pan-
European optical network, announced Alcatel on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The network will be run by the British Interoute
Telecommunications Group, one of Europe's largest
telecommunications groups. Europe's largest infrastructure of
telecommunications, it will link 70 cities in 17 countries by 20,
900 kilometers of fibers.(France-Telecommunications)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The Indonesian government has sent a task force to
East Timor to investigate a stoning incident which hurt seven
people and damaged the office of the U.N. Mission in East Timor (
UNAMET) in Maliana subdistrict.
</P>
<P>
The task force, which consists of officers of the Foreign
Affairs Ministry and related ministries, will join the Task Force
for the Direct Ballot in East Timor and UNAMET chief Ian Martin in
visiting Maliana on Wednesday, Defense Minister Gen. Wiranto said
Wednesday.(Indonesia-East Timor) 
