<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Puts Stress On Agricultural Technology and Innovation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji today
stressed the importance of scientific and technological reform by
being innovative in using technology in the agricultural and
engineering sectors.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, who also heads the State Leading Group for Promoting
Science, Technology and Education, chaired the 4th meeting of the
group and listened to reports made by related departments on the
drafting of the Program for Developing Agricultural Science and
Technology, the progressing of pilot projects for a nationwide
push on innovation in engineering and the development strategy of
China's high-energy physics sector.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting after listening to the reports, Zhu
pointed out that the advancement of agricultural science and
technology has played an outstanding role in solving China's food
problems, however the current systems and capabilities do not meet
the needs of modern agriculture.
</P>
<P>
As a result, he said, a program for developing agricultural
science and technology must be introduced as soon as possible to
improve efficiency, so as to ensure a continued development of
China's agricultural and rural economy in the new century.
</P>
</TEXT>
