<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Puts Stress On Agricultural Technology And Innovation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The decision made by the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China and the State Council to launch pilot projects on
intellectual innovation nationwide through the Chinese Academy of
Sciences (CAS) was an important step toward implementing the
strategies of revitalizing the nation through science and
education and pursuing sustainable development, Zhu said, adding
that the program has yielded fruitful results since its
implementation one year ago.
</P>
<P>
The premier called on those engaged in science and technology
to make unswerving efforts to accelerate scientific and
technological development, and urged further reinforcement of
reforms in this respect.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the importance of reform in science and
technology, declaring that the results of scientific research
should have high academic quality while at the same time
contributing to the overall benefit of society.
</P>
<P>
Vice-premiers Li Lanqing and Wen Jiabao also delivered
important speeches at the meeting which reviewed and approved on
principle the targets and contents of the Program for Developing
Agricultural Science and Technology. The meeting decided to
official start drafting the program.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting it was decided that a national working
conference on agricultural science and technology be convened at
an appropriate time to push ahead this task.
</P>
<P>
The meeting fully approved the results achieved by the pilot
projects for intellectual innovation launched through the CAS, and
put forth new requirements guiding further implementation of the
program. It also discussed the strategy for developing China's
high-energy physics as mapped out by the CAS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
