<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Open Consulate in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait will establish a
consulate general in China's Hong Kong Special Administration Area
(SAA) to take care of the Kuwaiti nationals and their interests
there.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to this effect was signed here on Wednesday by
Chinese Ambassador to Kuwait Zhang Zhixiang and Kuwaiti Foreign
Undersecretary Sulaiman Majid Al-Shahin, representing either
government.
</P>
<P>
Following the signing ceremony, Ambassador Zhang said the
Kuwaiti intention to open a consulate in Hong Kong was at first
included in a message to China's Vice Premier Qian Qichen from
Kuwaiti First Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Sabah
Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah shortly after Beijing resumed the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Zhang stressed that the Chinese government took the Kuwaiti
desire very seriously and agreed to let the Gulf country join the
first batch of nations friendly to China to set up consulates in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Al-Shahin said Kuwait has full confidence in
Hong Kong's prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
He voiced belief that to establish the consulate will help
boost commercial ties between Kuwait and Hong Kong, as well
as the overall bilateral relations between Kuwait and China.
</P>
