<HEADLINE> Eximbank Plays Big Role in Promoting Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The China Export and Import Bank (
Eximbank) has been playing a significant role in promoting China's
foreign trade and national economic development since it was
founded in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a ceremony marking the fifth anniversary of the
Eximbank today, the chairman and president of the bank, Yang Zilin,
said that it has made good use of policy-oriented financial means
to support the export of machinery and electronics products,
complete sets of equipment and other capital goods.
</P>
<P>
He said that by the end of May, the Eximbank had ratified
export sellers' credit totaling 76.29 billion yuan and 140 million
U.S. dollars, with 65.46 billion yuan and 130 million U.S. dollars
actually disbursed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the range of export business has developed from
sole project loans to medium- and short-term quota loans, overseas
project contracting loans, overseas business development loans and
overseas investment loans.
</P>
<P>
Other policy-oriented export financing businesses have also had
rapid development, he said. So far the bank has ratified 100
million U.S. dollars in export buyers' credit, provided 1.44
billion U.S. dollars in foreign trade guarantee, and accepted 1.64
billion U.S. dollars in export credit insurance.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, the Eximbank's total assets had reached 43.
75 billion yuan, he said, adding that the bank has opened nine
domestic representative offices and two overseas representative
offices.
</P>
<P>
It has also set up commission relationships with many domestic
commercial banks as well as 127 overseas banks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
