<HEADLINE> Sichuan Bans Export of Lumber </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Sichuan Provincial government
announced today that transportation of logged timber out of the
province will be banned as of July 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
The move is taken to further reduce the deprivation of the
natural forests that are officially under preservation orders,
according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The province's 4.63 million hectares of natural forests are now
under full protection, and tough measures have been taken to
combat illegal lumbering.
</P>
<P>
Deforestation was one of major factors in the flooding along
the Yangtze river last year, which caused huge losses in both
human lives and property. 
</P>
</TEXT>
