<HEADLINE> Eximbank Expertly Manages Government Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese government's concessional
loans to foreign countries and foreign governments' loans to China
have been very well managed by the China Export and Import Bank (
Eximbank) since it was authorized with this business.
</P>
<P>
At the occasion of the 5th anniversary of the Eximbank, the
chairman and president of the bank Yang Zilin said that by the end
of May, the bank has signed 42 agreements on Chinese government's
concessional credit to foreign countries, with a total volume of 2.
47 billion yuan (about 300 million U.S. dollars), benefiting 21
developing countries in Asia, Africa, Latin America and the South
Pacific Region.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that by supporting Chinese enterprises in their joint
ventures and cooperation with recipient countries in production
projects, the concessional loans have assisted the recipient
countries in their economic development and employment
opportunities, while at the same time providing the required
conditions for Chinese businesses to participate in transnational
operations.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bank has lent on foreign government loans worth
7.24 billion U.S. dollars for 262 projects, supporting a large
batch of key infrastructure projects in transportation, energy,
agriculture, forestry, water conservancy, environmental protection
and some other fields.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Eximbank will be even more active in
effectively carrying out government concessional loan projects,
and will do its best in using foreign government loans to promote
China's economic restructuring and a coordinated social and
economic development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
