<HEADLINE> Task Force Set Up to Tackle Qinghai Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Customs officials in northwest
China's Qinghai Province have set up a special anti-smuggling
police squad as part of its effort to strengthen its crackdown on
such illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
The Xining Branch of the Smuggling Cases Investigation Bureau
began work today and is the last of a number of such task forces
that have been established nationwide.
</P>
<P>
China's General Administration of Customs and Ministry of
Public Security are in charge of administration of the task forces,
which are authorized to investigate smuggling cases, arrest
suspects and conduct preliminary hearings.
</P>
<P>
Chen Liping, head of the Xining Customs Office, said that
smuggling activities cannot be ignored in the landlocked province
of Qinghai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
