<HEADLINE> Modern China Book Series A Landmark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- To celebrate the completion of a
major publishing project involving 150 books tracing the
historical development of contemporary China, a ceremony was held
in the Great Hall of the People here today attended by President
Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
The landmark work has taken fifteen years and more than 100,000
people have made inputs from all walks of life, including the army
and the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
The remarkable series, known as Modern China, contains 100
million Chinese characters and boasts 30,000 photographs. A laser
disc edition was also published this month.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin told representatives at today's
ceremony that the series provides rich historical material and
vivid lessons for the people.
</P>
<P>
"The people should fully utilize the results of the scientific
research this book series provides to serve the purposes of
improving the government, developing talents and pushing forward
the reform, opening up and modernization drive," he said.
</P>
<P>
The book series, he stressed, sums up the experiences and
lessons of the People's Republic of China over the past five
decades.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Li Lanqing also attended the ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
