<HEADLINE> Jiang Criticizes Party Members Losing Socialist Path </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China's top state and Party leader
Jiang Zemin has criticized some Party members who lost the correct
political direction due to weakened political faith and lack of a
correct world outlook.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, general secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Central Committee, made the remarks at a forum held here on June
28 to mark the 78th anniversary of the CPC's founding.
</P>
<P>
"A Party member, especially an official, should firmly adhere
to socialism and communism as his fundamental political conviction,
as well as Marxist dialectical materialism and historical
materialism as his outlook of world," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"If he is diffident in regard to these factors, he will surely
drift off the correct political direction," he said.
</P>
<P>
While pointing out the misbehavior of some Party members, Jiang
acknowledged that "some comrades' confidence about the final
victory over capitalism by socialism and the future of the
construction of socialism with Chinese characteristics has been
weakened".
</P>
<P>
"Some people, lacking spiritual ballast, have led a life of
debauchery, or tried to find spiritual sustenance in feudalistic
superstitions and other kinds of negative behavior. Some pursuing
personal interests have drifted with the money-worshiping tide and
even grabbed state property by taking advantage of their official
positions."
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that education in political faith among Party
members and officials should be unceasingly enhanced. "Otherwise,
our ideological front will be occupied by non-proletarian
ideologies. We must remember and pay full attention to this lesson
that history has taught us." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
