<HEADLINE> EDS-Recast Jiang on Analysis of International Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government will
continue to look on both the domestic and international situations
with dialectical conceptions of Marxism, said president Jiang
Zemin recently.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and the
Chinese central government have dealt with the recent issue
concerning NATO's interference in Yugoslavia's internal affairs
and NATO's attack on the Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia according
to the domestic and international situations and have implemented
correct principles and policies.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee, made his
remarks at a meeting which was held in Beijing on June 28 to mark
the 78th anniversary of the founding of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
He said that when the situation is good, people should notice
the existing problems and try to solve them promptly. When facing
trouble and setbacks, people should see the bright future and have
full confidence in winning victory. When facing challenges, people
should calm down and deal with the challenges after careful
consideration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
