<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada to Import U.S. Bomb-grade Uranium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Two Canadian companies have
acquired U.S. permission to import bomb-grade uranium from the
country for making medical isotopes, Canadian media said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under a five-year contract approved Tuesday by the U.S. Nuclear
Regulatory Commission (NRC), Canadian manufacturers Atomic Energy
of Canada Ltd.(AECL) and MDS Nordion will import 130 kilograms of
highly enriched uranium.
</P>
<P>
The highly enriched uranium, which can be easily converted to
nuclear weapons, is to be used at new MAPLE reactors and in a new
processing facility under construction at the AECL Chalk River,
Ontario, to produce molybdenum-99, an isotope used in the medical
industry.
</P>
<P>
While insisting on yearly reports on the companies' steps to
convert highly enriched uranium to low-enriched, NRC praised
Canada's nuclear non-proliferation policy as "exemplary."
</P>
<P>
The exports would constitute no threat to "the common defense
and security of the United States," NRC was quoted as concluding
in making its decision.
</P>
<P>
The permission came after MDS Nordion executives told NRC on
June 16 that the company might be unable to continue making
medical isotopes after next year because of the uncertainty over
the imports.
</P>
<P>
Ottawa-based MDS Nordion is one of the world's leading
suppliers of several key isotopes, which are used in radiation
therapy, imaging and medical diagnosis to detect and measure heart
attacks, treat prostate and thyroid cancer, and to identify blood
clots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990630.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetans Get Blessing from 11th Panchen Lama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIGAZE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- More than 16,000 people in Tibet
Autonomous Region paid homage to and received blessing from the
11th Panchen Lama during a three day head touching ritual which
ended today.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the nine year old Erdeni Losang
Qamba Lhunzhub Qoigyijabu, the 11th Panchen Lama, has blessed so
many people at one time.
</P>
<P>
The exact number of the people who received his blessing was 16,
168, some of whom came from as far as Yunnan, Sichuan and Qinghai
provinces, a local religious official said.
</P>
<P>
He said that from the excitement and happy expressions on the
faces of the blessed lamas, farmers and herdspeople, the 11th
Panchen Lama enjoys great support from the local people.
</P>
<P>
The 11th Panchen Lama was selected as the reincarnation of the
10th Panchen Lama during a lot drawing ceremony held in front of a
statue of the Buddha Sakyamuni in late 1995 and the State Council
approved the selection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
