<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Public confidence in Hong Kong's
economy was much stronger in June this year than it was a year ago,
according to a survey published on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The survey on economic confidence indices across Hong Kong,
conducted by the Hong Kong Policy Research Institute, showed that
economic indices in July 1998 were lower than those in July 1997,
but in June 1999 economic confidence was much stronger than in
June 1998.
</P>
<P>
The most significant example was confidence towards the
improvement on the unemployment situation in Hong Kong. It dropped
in July 1998, but resumed considerably in June 1999.
</P>
<P>
In the fields of "economic prospects of Hong Kong", "stock
market", and "property market", the public confidence indices all
increased in June this year compared with July last year.
</P>
<P>
The institute began to conduct the surveys in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
