<HEADLINE> Australian Shares End Financial Year Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Australian shares ignored an
overnight surge on Wall Street to close lower on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index gave up 22.4 points to end at 2,968.9
after an afternoon of wild price fluctuations inspired by the
close of the financial year.
</P>
<P>
Trade was volatile over the day with the all ordinaries index
trading in a wide range from a high of 3,008.5, hit in the
morning, to a low of 2,956.2 struck half an hour before the close.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index closed 40.0 lower at 5,188.1 and the
all resources index softened 8.2 to 1,209.8.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was a healthy 650.9 million shares worth 1.432 billion
Australian dollars (945 million U.S. dollars) with 724 issues
falling, 728 rising and 469 stocks steady.
</P>
<P>
Local banking stocks were lower as concerns about the timing of
an expected U.S. interest rate rise weakened enthusiasm for the
majors.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank slipped 44 cents to 25.00 Australian
dollars, ANZ lost 24.7 cents to 11.109 Australian dollars, Westpac
surrendered 22 to 9.80 Australian dollars and Commonwealth lost 19
to 24.05 Australian dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
