<HEADLINE> Philippines to Send Small Team to SEA Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Olympic Committee (
POC) general assembly approved on Wednesday a 306-man Philippine
delegation for next month's Souhthest Asian Games, the smallest
squad from the country since the 1983 Singapore event.
</P>
<P>
The number includes 179 male and 65 female athletes, 45 coaches,
six team officials, four technical men, and seven delegation
officials.
</P>
<P>
New POC president Celso Dayrit said they are expecting to win
medals from at least five sports events which include cycling,
athletics, billiards, karatedo and taekwando.
</P>
<P>
Despite the small delegation, the POC officials remained
optimistic the country will win more than 20 gold medals.
</P>
<P>
Aside from the above five sports, the Philippines will also
compete in badminton, basketball, boxing, football, golf, pencak
silat, sepak takraw, squash, shooting, swimming (including diving
water polo), table tennis, lawn tennis, tenpin bowling and
traditional boat race.
</P>
<P>
The PSC has allotted 10 million pesos (250,000 million U.S.
dollars) for the country's participation in the 20th SEA Games to
be held on August 8-15 in Brunei Darussalam. 
</P>
