<HEADLINE> Chinese, Cambodian FMs Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China has always maintained that
the Khmer Rouge issue is part of Cambodia's internal affairs, and
it believes that the Cambodian government and people can
independently make judgments and decisions to properly settle all
such internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Foreign minister Tang Jiaxuan made the remarks here today in
talks with Hor Nam Hong, Cambodia's senior minister and minister
of foreign affairs and international cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong briefed Tang on the Cambodian government's
principled stance on the Khmer Rouge issue, stressing that it is
imperative for the Cambodian government and people to
independently settle the issue.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, the two sides expressed satisfaction with the
development momentum of bilateral ties. They also agreed that the
two countries should further promote cooperation in politics, the
economy, trade, culture, education and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that the positive changes in Cambodia's situation
will be conducive to the growth of exchanges and cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the leaders of the two countries have reached
agreement on the promotion of Sino-Cambodian traditional
friendship and cooperation oriented toward the 21st century, and
they should implement the common understanding and deepen
cooperation in all areas in a practical manner.
</P>
<P>
Tang also expressed his appreciation for the Cambodian
government's adherence to the "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong confirmed that in his view bilateral ties have
been good, and stressed that Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen's
successful visit to China last February has positively promoted
mutual understanding and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the political situation in Cambodia is stable, and
economic rehabilitation has been carried out, adding that the
Cambodian government and people highly value Sino-Cambodian
friendly ties, and are keen to make efforts to promote mutually
beneficial cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Tang and Hor Nam Hong also exchanged views on the current
regional situation and the forthcoming ASEAN forum meetings.
</P>
</TEXT>
