<HEADLINE> Egyptian Firms to Invest in Rwanda: Ambassador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 30 (Xinhua) - A number of Egyptian companies have
shown their interest in investing in Rwanda, the Rwanda News
Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Egyptian companies are finalizing contacts to start
investments in Rwanda in different areas like Lake Kivu Methane
Gas extraction project, Free Trade Zones, Hotels, Health , Road
Construction and Power Supply to the Kigali city," Omar said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ambassador disclosed that a number of business
people and enterprises from Egypt will engage in the first
Egyptian trade exhibition in Rwandan capital Kigali due from July
1 to 8 this year.
</P>
<P>
"The number of business companies to attend which have so far
registered is estimated to be 20,'' Egyptian Ambassador to Rwanda
Muna Omar was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The products at the exhibition will include; furniture-rugs
and carpets, electrical appliances, leather- tanning products,
medicines, agricultural tools, textiles, garments, kitchenware,
hand-crafts and stationery," ambassador Omar indicated.
</P>
<P>
Deputy chief of mission at the Egyptian Embassy in Kigali,
Ahmed Bakr, said that the trade exhibition is aimed at promoting
trade between Egypt and Rwanda, increasing economic relations in
all fields between the two nations and giving Rwandan business
people an idea of Egyptian products.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Rwanda and Egypt have witnessed continued
improvement since April 1998 when 20 Rwandan business people and
state-run enterprises visited Egypt to promote commercial
exchanges between the two countries. 
</P>
