<HEADLINE> MOFTEC Encourages Training of Overseas Investment Personnel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Enterprises involved in overseas
investment business have been urged to pay close attention to the
training of their personnel by the Chinese Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
"Government departments should create a flexible environment
for enterprises, provide them information on overseas markets and
coordinate training workshops," said Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of
foreign trade and economic cooperation, at the closing ceremony of
the second workshop to promote Chinese investment overseas, which
was sponsored by MOFTEC and the State Economic and Trade
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Sun asked the 61 participants from relevant enterprises in 20
provinces and cities to focus on market research, policy study,
technology advantages and personnel selection in their overseas
investment strategies.
</P>
<P>
He also encouraged a further 32 participants, who will take
part in a three month intensive French and Spanish training
courses, to study hard.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, China had set up 5,600 ventures in 160
countries and regions, with combined contractual investment from
the Chinese side exceeding 600 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to MOFTEC sources, Chinese investment overseas is
mainly in trade, resources development, processing, transportation,
contracted construction projects, and food services.  
</P>
