<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Fall 1.7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks plunged 233.35
points, or 1.7 percent while China plays maintained the momentum
of increase Wednesday before a one-day break Thursday to observe a
public holiday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index finished at 13,532.14.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover continued to be robust and stood at 12.042
billion HK dollars (1.544 billion U.S. dollars), 1.239 billion HK
dollars (159 million U.S. dollars) more than that of Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sub-indices Finance, Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP;
Industry all suffered losses of between 1.12 percent and 2.14
percent.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares continued to gain as the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations
Index registered increases of 1.66 percent and 0.86 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The share prices fell 78.37 points, or 0.57 percent, to open at
13,687.12 Wednesday and finished the morning session at 13,772.96.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index lost 74.8 points, or 0.54 percent, to close
at 13,765.49 Tuesday. 
</P>
