<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rain-Struck Railways Back On Line In Guizhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fierce rainstorms battered both the eastern and western parts
of Guizhou starting yesterday through to early this morning.
</P>
<P>
As much as 225 mm of rain has fallen on areas along the
Xiangqian (from Hunan to Guizhou), the Guikun (from Guizhou to
Kunming) and the Qiangui(from Guizhou to Guangxi) railroads in
Guizhou.
</P>
<P>
The rainstorms have caused several landslides, with some parts
of the railways submerged by floodwaters. And this led to the
suspension of 15 pairs of passenger trains on the three routes.
</P>
<P>
According to sources with the Guiyang Railway Bureau, all
trains moving out from Guiyang Station will be able to resume
normal operations before midnight tonight.
</P>
<P>
However, the weather forecast is for rain to continue over the
next few days. Rescue teams are on guard against more flooding.
</P>
<P>
Continuous rainstorms have hit many provinces and autonomous
regions in southern China, while a heatwave is plaguing the
northern part. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
