<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Urges Party to Emphasize Its Political Strength </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China (CPC)
must emphasize its Marxist political stance linked to socialism
with Chinese characteristics in order to maintain benefits for the
people, China's President Jiang Zemin urged today.
</P>
<P>
As general secretary of the CPC Central Committee, Jiang made
his plea when addressing a forum today marking the 78th
anniversary of the founding of Party.
</P>
<P>
Throughout its existence the CPC has led the Chinese people as
they made great strides forward and achievements in the country's
successful revolution against feudalism, re-construction, and also
importantly in the later reform and opening up policy.
</P>
<P>
"The key reason for the Party's success is its perseverance in
building itself ideologically, politically and organizationally
and in its work style under the guidance of Marxism," Jiang
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that without a political program, an aim or a party
line, then a party can no longer be regarded as a political
organization.
</P>
<P>
"As a dedicated Marxist party, the CPC with more than 60
million members must hold on to an appropriate political stance,
abide by the Party's disciplinary procedure and requirements and
strengthen political sensitivity and awareness, thus guaranteeing
the unity of the Party ideologically, politically and
organizationally," added Jiang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
