<HEADLINE> Ban on Overseas Investment in Saunas and Massage Parlors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Overseas businesspeople have
been banned by starting up solely-funded business related to
certain types of entertainment, including saunas and massage
parlors, by south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at wiping out what officials described in a
recent notice as the increase in the "evil social phenomena of
pornography, gambling and drugs".
</P>
<P>
In the notice, the Guangdong Provincial Party Committee and
Guangdong Provincial Government also urged restraint in allowing
Sino-foreign joint ventures to set up such business enterprises.
</P>
<P>
According to the notice, the management over massage and saunas
parlors, hotels, and ballrooms as well as book shops and audio-
visual publications shops will be strengthened.  
</P>
</TEXT>
