<HEADLINE> No Price Hikes During World Horticulture Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan
provincial government will take a series of measures to ensure no
price hikes in its important tourism industry during the ongoing '
99 Kunming World Horticulture Exposition which opened on May 1st
in Kunming, the capital of the province.
</P>
<P>
"The provincial government will further strengthen supervision
to ensure that prices linked to food, hotels, recreation, goods
and transportation will remain the same as that of last year,"
Yunnan governor Li Jiating said in an exclusive interview with
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Since its opening over 50 days ago, the exposition has received
nearly 1.5 million domestic and overseas visitors and even more
are expected to arrive with the summer vacations.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that prices within the province's tourism
industry were actually a little bit lower in the past two months
compared with the same period of previous years.
</P>
<P>
The horticulture exposition, the seventh of its kind, will run
to October 31 and is expected to attract 10 million visitors.
</P>
</TEXT>
