<DOCNO> XIE19990630.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Parliament Passes Budget for 1999-2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi Parliament Wednesday
passed the budget for the 1999-2000 fiscal year starting from July
1, 1999, which was presented by Finance Minister A.M.S. Kibria on
June 10.
</P>
<P>
The total revenue in the fiscal year was proposed to be 240.26
billion taka (about 4.95 billion U.S. dollars) while the
expenditure was estimated at 361.78 billion taka (about 7.47
billion dollars). The budget deficit will be supplemented by
external sources such as foreign grants, foreign borrowing and
domestic sources.
</P>
<P>
The parliament Tuesday passed the Finance Bill, 1999,
authorizing the government to collect the proposed amount and to
expend the estimated amount, 22.5 percent and 12.6 percent higher
respectively than those in the revised budget of the 1998-1999
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
In the new budget, the outlay of the annual development program
 stands at 155 billion taka (about 3.2 billion dollars), 13.9
percent higher than the current fiscal year's original allocation
and 10.7 percent higher than the revised allocation.
</P>
<P>
The target of the economic growth rate for the new fiscal year
has been set at 6.5 percent, 1.3 percentage points higher than the
growth rate of 5.2 percent for the outgoing fiscal, according to
the finance minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
