<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Reduces Anti-Duty for Thai Canned Pineapples </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Commerce Department has
reduced anti-duty (AD) rates on Thai canned pineapples to between
3.26 percent and 24.6 percent, the Thai News Agency reported on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Director-General of the Department of Foreign Trade of
the Thai Commerce Ministry Sumitra Vorakulchalerm was quoted as
saying the department received an announcement of the U.S.
Commerce Department, informing its third review of AD rates on
imports of Thai canned pineapples.
</P>
<P>
The rates were reduced from between 1.73 percent and 51.2
percent and between 0.5 percent to 55.8 percent, she said.
</P>
<P>
"The latest rates are the preliminary determination of the U.S.
Commerce Department's third review of the issue while its final
determination is scheduled to be announced in September," she
said.
</P>
<P>
A decision on whether Washington would continue to impose AD on
imports of Thai canned pineapples would be revealed at the
September review, she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
