<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices ended lower on
Singapore Stock Market Wednesday amid profit-taking selling before
the close of the U.S. Federal Reserve meeting which is expected to
raise interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) was down 13.38 points
to close at 2,167.7.
</P>
<P>
Total volume decreased to some 1.929 billion shares valued at
2.018 billion Singapore dollars (about 1.186 billion U.S.
dollars). Losers led gainers by 216 to 131 with 99 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
IPC remained the most active stock with a turnover of 86.47
million shares. It was followed by Samudera which had 78.47
million units done. Frt Links was next with 49.58 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS and DBS F led gainers of the day earning 70 cents to close
at 18.2 and 20.8 Singapore dollars respectively. SPH 100 gained 60
cents to finish at 29.3 Singapore dollars. Nobel Des rose 46 cents
to end at 1.28 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Venture was the biggest loser of the day with
a loss of 90 cents at 13.1 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sen and SIA F
lost 50 cents to finish at 18.8 and 16.2 Singapore dollars
respectively. GE Life and OUB F each lost 30 cents to finish at
22.7 and 8.2 Singapore dollars separately.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that in early trading the key index had climbed as
much as 22.35 points to 2,203.43, breaking the all-time closing
high of 2,191.73 following an overnight rally on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
