<HEADLINE> China's Auto Manufacturing Slowing Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China's automobile industry
suffered a slowdown in growth in May, according to official
statistics, with the output rate for cars standing at 6.5 percent
on a year-on-year basis and that for trucks at a negative two
percent.
</P>
<P>
During the month, the country produced 50,900 cars and 73,900
trucks, said the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).
</P>
<P>
The NBS expects that car manufacturing will keep a low growth
rate this year, partly because China has raised its standards for
eliminating car pollution and that there will be a sluggish
consumer demand.
</P>
<P>
The bureau also blamed the slowing down of industry and
investment in fixed assets for the drop in truck output.
</P>
<P>
However, against the trend, northeast China's Jilin province,
one of China's major automobile bases, enjoyed a 25-percent growth
rate for its car industry in May, taking the lead in the country,
said the bureau. 
</P>
</TEXT>
