<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, chairman of the All-
China Federation of Trade Unions (ACFTU), said today that the
substantive exchange between Chinese and Japanese trade unions has
increased the mutual understanding and reinforced bilateral
cooperation in the work of trade unions.
</P>
<P>
Wei, also a member of the Political Bureau Standing Committee
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, made the
remarks during a meeting here this afternoon with a delegation
from Japan's International Labor Foundation (JILF) headed by its
president Shimitsu Haruki.
</P>
