The ACFTU has sent five delegations to Japan to study the
useful experience of Japanese trade unions over the past two years,
while JILF has also sent professionals to lecture the Chinese side
on Japan's operations in coordinating the labor relationship, Wei
said, adding that such exchange has been welcomed by ACFTU cadres
at all levels.
</P>
<P>
Shimitsu Haruki said that the exchange between JILF and ACFTU
has been going smoothly in the past three years and the exchange
in coordinating the labor relationship has been effective.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese side is interested in the characteristics of the
workers' representative conference system in Chinese enterprises
and hopes that cooperation between the trade unions of the two
countries would be expanded. 
