<HEADLINE> Philippines Needs Better Post-Harvest Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Agriculture Secretary
Edgardo Angara stressed the need to prioritize post-harvest
facilities to reduce the considerable loss of grains.
</P>
<P>
Angara said that due to lack of efficient dryers, warehouses
and other post-harvest facilities, the nation loses 1 million tons
of grains each year, Philippine News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At present, the average rice importation of the country is
600,000 tons annually.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he disclosed that the fishery sector loses around
400,000 tons yearly for lack of cold storage and other
post-harvest requirement.
</P>
<P>
"If we can save the 20 to 40 percent of production of fish, we
can certainly hope to be self-sufficient in fish," he said.
</P>
<P>
Thus, he emphasized, "we shall encourage the use of more
efficient post-harvest facilities including cold storage,
mechanical dryers for rice and corn." 
</P>
</TEXT>
