<HEADLINE> Three Stocks Suspended on Chinese Stock Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The stocks of three companies
listed on the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges are suspended
from today on, as they have reported losses for three consecutive
years, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
According to their 1998 performance reports released today, the
Shanghai Shuanglu Electric Appliances Co. Ltd. and the SAIC
Multiple Trading Co. Ltd., both listed on the Shanghai Stock
Exchanges, recorded a loss of 11.90 million yuan and 109.67
million yuan, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Chongqing Yu-Gang Titanium Dioxide Co. Ltd., listed on the
Shenzhen Stock Exchanges, reported a loss of 348.87 million yuan
in 1998.
</P>
