<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops New Corn Strain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China is accelerating the breeding
and development of a new corn strain, known as black corn, to
enrich domestic resources.
</P>
<P>
So far, a batch of the black corn variety has been planted in
dozens of hectares of land in north and northeast China provinces,
according to an expert from the Chinese Academy of Agricultural
Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Foodstuffs using black sweet corn such as bread and noodles are
now on sale in a number of shops in some large cities such as
Beijing and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The essential elements, which include proteins, amino acid and
other trace elements, such as calcium and selenium, are 50 to 150
percent higher than those in common corn strains, according to
China's Food Testing Center.
</P>
<P>
Industry experts expressed great interest in the new strain
when the Huafeng Xinyuan Corporation first introduced it from Peru
five years ago. As a major corn producer and consumer, China
expects great potential for its corn industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
