<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Overseas Tourism Revenue Up 14 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua)-- China received 28.83 million
overseas tourists during the first five months of this year,
earning some 5.72 billion US dollars, up 14.05 percent and 14.88
percent respectively on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
In the period, there were more than the average number of
tourists from 15 worldwide countries, except Russia and Mongolia,
traveling to China, according to a report by the National Tourism
Administration.
</P>
<P>
Due to the recovery of their economies, the number of tourists
from the Republic of Korea and other countries in Southeast Asia
surpassed the 1997 figures.
</P>
<P>
Tourists from the United States and Canada both rose by nearly
ten percent on an annual basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
