<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Expects Bumper Harvest Of Early Season Rice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The island province of Hainan in
southernmost China is expecting a bumper harvest of early season
rice this year, with an estimated overall rice production of 850,
000 tons, 12,000 tons more than the previous year and a new all
time high.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the Hainan Provincial Department
of Agriculture, the province planted a total of 2.58 million mu (
172,000 hectares) of early season rice, and half of the land was
seeded with high-quality rice breeds.
</P>
<P>
"We devoted a total of one million mu (66,000 ha) of land to
the growing of hybrid rice, whose output is higher than that of
ordinary rice by some 50 to 57 kilograms per mu," said the
official.
</P>
<P>
He also attributed the island's bumper harvest to a timely and
effective prevention of rice diseases and insect pests.
</P>
<P>
The reaping of rice across the island is expected to be
completed within the next couple of days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
