<HEADLINE> Guangdong Retail Sales Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 30 (Xinhua)-- South China's Guangdong Province
had a retail sales volume of 140.73 billion yuan during the
January-May period, up 8.7 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The provincial statistics bureau said in a report that retail
sales in the rural area was more brisk than in the urban areas,
with a growth rate of 10.3 percent on a yearly basis, which is 2.2
percentage points higher than the rate for the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the higher-than-usual temperature helped
buoy up the retail sales.
</P>
<P>
The province's retail price index and consumer price index
dropped to 3.8 percent and 2.4 percent respectively during the
five month period, on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the provincial industry had an added value of 96.83
billion yuan, up 12.3 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
