<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang to Invest More in Building Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region in northwest China is to invest 17.2 billion yuan in the
next five years in building highways.
</P>
<P>
A senior official from the regional communication department
said recently that by the end of 1998, there were 320,000
registered auto vehicles in the region which carried 200 million
passengers and transported 250 billion tons of freight over the
past few years, accounting for 95 percent and 83 percent of the
region's total transportation volume respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the region has spent 9 billion yuan
building highways over the past two decades, 10 times the
investment of the 30 years before 1979.
</P>
<P>
At present, Xinjiang has a total highway mileage of 32,000 km.
</P>
</TEXT>
