billion HK dollars (2.298 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
This was announced by the government of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region Wednesday in its financial results for the
two months ending May 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Expenditure for the first two months of the current financial
year amounted to some 42.114 billion HK dollars (5.399 billion U.S.
dollars) and revenue to 24.186 billion HK dollars (3.101 billion U.
S. dollars), resulting in a deficit of almost 17.928 billion HK
dollars (2.298 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The fiscal reserves stood at 416.375 billion HK dollars (53.381
billion U.S. dollars) at May 31, 1999, a decrease of 17.928
billion HK dollars (2.298 billion U.S. dollars) compared with the
balance at March 31, 1999, the end of the previous financial year.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said the government's accounts were
prepared on a cash basis and reflected the incidence of receipts
and payments during the period.
</P>
<P>
"The results are in line with our expectations, based on the
budgeted deficit for the year of 36.5 billion HK dollars (4.68
billion U.S. dollars) as announced by the financial secretary in
his budget speech on March 3, 1999," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
