<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 09:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 12 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A total of 12 rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed on Tuesday by
the Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey, an official
statement said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said the Turkish security forces clashed with the PKK in
Havillati Mountain region in Yuksekova town of Hakkari province
bordering Iran.
</P>
<P>
One PKK guerrilla was captured in Omerli town of Mardin province
and one PKK militant surrendered to the security forces in
Baskale town of Van province, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Turkey's Ankara State Security Court sentenced PKK
leader Abdullah Ocalan to death for treason.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan-led PKK has been fighting since 1984 a war for an
independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey. Conflicts
between the Turkish security forces and the PKK militants have
claimed over 37,000 lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
