<HEADLINE> Tanzania Among Major African Textiles Exporters to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania has become a major
African textile exporter to the United States, a newspaper said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Garment exports from Tanzania to the U.S. market reached
193,000 square meters in the first quarter of this year, an amount
ranking seventh in the region, according to the Dar es
Salaam-based Financial Times.
</P>
<P>
During the period, South Africa led with 5.37 million square
meters of cloth. Mauritius was second with 3.059 million square
meters and Lesotho ranked third with 2.232 million square meters,
the paper cited statistics of the U.S. customs service as
reporting.
</P>
<P>
Kenya rose to number four with exports of 775,000 square meters
of woven shirts and trousers. It is followed by Madagascar,
Swaziland, Tanzania, Nigeria and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Tanzania was eighth among ten Sub-Saharan countries
with significant exports to the United States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
