<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Visits Container Terminals in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
made a tour of Hong Kong's Kwai Chung Container Terminals
Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, one of the world's busiest container ports, handled
14.7 million TEUs (twenty-foot equivalent units) in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Hu came here from Shenzhen Tuesday to attend the unveiling
ceremony of the Reunification Monument on the second anniversary
of Hong Kong's return to China. 
</P>
