<HEADLINE> China Eastern Airlines Develops Internal Maintenance Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Airlines (CEA), one
of the nation's three major air carriers, has introduced an
internal maintenance program and plans to overhaul four Airbus 300
aircraft in 1999, according to CEA President Li Zhongming.
</P>
<P>
 Li said that the success of the company's program to overhaul
large Airbus aircraft will effectively end China's dependence of
foreign maintenance.
</P>
<P>
 The overhaul program includes 490 regular structural and 44
supplementary items, as well as painting and changing parts,
according to Li. He said that the first aircraft will be
overhauled in 42 days.
</P>
<P>
 Li also noted that the overhaul project for the second
aircraft will be completed in 35 days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
