<HEADLINE> China to Host World Automation Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Third World Congress on
Intelligent Control and Automation will be held at the China
University of Science and Technology(CUST) in Hefei, capital of
east China's Anhui Province, between June 28-July 2 next year.
</P>
<P>
Some 400 scholars from some 10 countries and regions, including
the United States, England, Canada, Australia and Singapore, are
expected to attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Sun Demin, president of the organizing committee and a
professor of CUST, said that the goal of the congress is to
promote exchanges of new research findings in intelligent control
and automation.
</P>
<P>
A large number of Chinese entrepreneurs are also expected to
attend the event.
</P>
<P>
The congress was initiated in 1993 to serve people of Chinese
origin. However, a number of foreign scientists attended the first
two congresses held at Qinghua University in Beijing and the Xi'an
Jiaotong University.  
</P>
</TEXT>
