<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru Beats Japan, Paraguay Draws Bolivia at Copa America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Peru defeated Japan while
Paraguay and Bolivia drew goalless in Group A on the opening day
of the Copa America soccer tournament in Paraguay on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Holsen scored twice in an eight-minute span to boost
Peru to the 3-2 victory over the Asian guest Japan in the opener
in Asuncion, the Paraguayan capital.
</P>
<P>
Holsen scored in the 74th and 82nd minutes but it was Japan who
scored the opening in the sixth minute through a Wagner Lopes
header.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Soto scored in the 70th minute to equalize for Peru
before Holsen netted his first goal to put Peru ahead.
</P>
<P>
A free kick from Japan's Atsuhiro Miura evened the score in the
78th minute. But Holsen's deciding goal came as he headed in off a
centering pass from Flavio Maestri.
</P>
<P>
For the host Paraguay, scoring opportunities abounded when they
met Bolivia but what they lacked were the finishing touch.
</P>
<P>
Striker Roque Santa Cruz had several good looks at the goal,
but was repeatedly denied by Bolivian goalkeeper Jose Fernandez.
</P>
<P>
A free kick by Edwin Sanchez in the 15th minute was Bolivia's
best chance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
