<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Developed Nations Blamed for Environmental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan State Minister for
Environment Kezimbira Miyingo has said that developed countries
should be blamed for the global environmental degradation.
</P>
<P>
The minister made the remarks when opening a climate change
project inception workshop at the International Conference Center
here Tuesday, the New Vision paper said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Developed countries' unsustainable pattern of consumption has
largely caused problems, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he urged for integrated and concerted efforts in
combating environmental problems because this is a global problem
and threatens to permanently change global weather and climate
with serious consequences on human activities.
</P>
<P>
He said western Uganda was already hit by severe drought.
Animal and crop production in the region had slumped due to lack
of rainfall.
</P>
<P>
Cattle were dying for lack of water and pasture. The government
had already received reports of banana plants drying up in the
gardens, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
