<HEADLINE> U.N. Command, DPRK Representatives to Meet Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Representatives from the United
Nations Command (UNC) and the People's Army of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) will meet at the truce village
of Panmunjom on Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
"The United Nations Command has accepted an invitation from the
North Korean People's Army to meet at 10 a.m., Friday, July 2, at
Panmunjom," said a press release issued by the UNC on Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is seen as a continuation of the high-level talks
on the recent armed conflict in the Yellow Sea.
</P>
<P>
On June 15, a DPRK torpedo boat was sunk and three others badly
damaged while two South Korean patrol ships were slightly damaged
in an inter-Korean exchange of fire.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming meeting will also be the eighth general
officers' meeting since the talks began in March 1998.
</P>
<P>
The talks were designed to discuss practical armistice-related
issues and to reduce tension on the Korean Peninsula. 
</P>
</TEXT>
