<HEADLINE> China's Third Largest Gold Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi Province
has jumped from 14th to third place nationwide in terms of annual
gold production, with last year's output topping 11.95 tons.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi has abundant gold resources. Gold mines operate in six
of the 10 prefectures located mainly in the Hanjiang and
Jialingjiang river valleys and the Qinling Mountain Range.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has invested 350 million yuan in gold
exploration since 1985, said Sun Qianshan, an official with the
Shaanxi Gold Industry Bureau, adding that the province has proven
reserves of some 340 tons.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi currently has 40 state-owned gold mining companies,
including the first venture established in Tongguan County in 1978.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
