<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 41 Fire Cases Reported in Myanmar in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A total of 41 fires broke out in
Myanmar in May, dropping by 56 cases or 57.7 percent as compared
with the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The fires destroyed 315 houses, injured two people and left
1,571 homeless, the official evening newspaper City News reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 34 or 82.92 percent were due to negligence or
were kitchen fires, it said, giving no details of the property
losses during the month.
</P>
<P>
The authorities are maintaining fire prevention measures in the
 entire country even during the five-month-long rainy season which
 started in June.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, a total of 382 fire cases
occurred in Myanmar in the first quarter of this year, destroying
1,326 houses, killing 13 people and leaving 5,665 people homeless.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
