<HEADLINE>   One Killed, Nine Hurt in Explosion in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed while nine
others were wounded when a powerful handgrenade exploded Tuesday
night in Basilan Province in the southern Philippines, a police
report coming here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the explosion happened in a elementary
school in Maluso town when a group of people were attending a
religious ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation showed a group of persons lobbed and
exploded the powerful handgrenade in the midst of the religious
services, killing at least one person and injuring nine others.
</P>
<P>
All the victims were immediately rushed to the Basilan
Community Hospital for emergency treatment and the police is
conducting further investigation of the accident, the report said.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
