<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The China Ocean Shipping
Corporation (COSCO) has opened a new weekly international
container route from Taicang Port in east China's Jiangsu Province
to the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
A Korean container ship with a 430 TEU (ton equivalent unit)
handling capacity will serve as the major carrier on the new route
which departs Taicang Port bound for the ROK every Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
