<HEADLINE> Sanya Announces Port Modernization Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The city of Sanya in Hainan
Province recently announced plans to build one of the largest
modern fishing ports in south China.
</P>
<P>
Sanya produces 100,000 tons of fish annually and is the major
fish and marine products distribution center in Hainan, China's
southernmost island province.
</P>
<P>
The city government plans to allocate 198.5 million yuan for a
project to modernize Liudaowan Bay. Plans call for the
construction of 10 berths with an annual handling capacity of 100,
000 tons in the near future. A long-term plan has called for the
construction of 30 berths capable of handling 3,000 fishing boats
with an annual handling capacity of 300,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The port will be equipped with state-of-the-art service
facilities and water, oil and ice supply systems. 
