<HEADLINE> Latin America, EU Promise to Work for Higher U.N. Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Latin America and the
European Union (EU) countries pledged here on Tuesday to work
together for the improvement of the efficiency of the United
Nations.
</P>
<P>
The promise was expressed in the "Priorities for Action" plan
signed by the heads of state and government attending the first
summit of Latin America, EU and Caribbean countries.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to cooperate closely on the exchange of views so
that the U.N. may work more efficiently in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
They also promised to strengthen the role of the world body
under the propositions and principles of the U.N. Charter.
</P>
</TEXT>
