<HEADLINE> German Chancellor Supports Second Latin America-EU Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Gerhard
Schroeder announced here on Tuesday that Germany would accept
Spain's invitation to attend the second Latin American, European
Union and Caribbean Summit scheduled for 2002 in Spain.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder told a press conference after the end of the first
Latin America-EU summit that all the participating countries have
realized that there should not be a lull between the two summits.
</P>
<P>
Schroeder said he has experienced things at the current summit
that will be of great benefit to the implementation of the
agreements between the Southern Common Market and the EU.
</P>
<P>
He also defended the participation of Cuba in the negotiations
between Latin America, the Caribbean and the EU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
