<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Meets Leaders of Central Institutions in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
met here Wednesday morning with leading members of the central
government institutions and mainland-funded enterprises in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Among them were Jiang Enzhu, director of the Xinhua News Agency
Hong Kong Branch; Ma Yuzhen, commissioner of the Ministry of
Foreign Affairs in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR); and Xiong Ziren, commander of the People's Liberation Army
Forces in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Hu urged these institutions and enterprises to
implement the "one country, two systems" policy, abide by the
Basic Law and the laws of the HKSAR, and respect and support the
work of the SAR government under Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao came to Hong Kong from Shenzhen Tuesday morning for
the unveiling of the Reunification Monument on the second
anniversary of Hong Kong's return to China. 
</P>
