<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Latin America, EU Advocate Fairer Free Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Leaders attending the Latin
America-European Union (EU) summit on Tuesday called for the
establishment of a fairer free trade system with rules acceptable
to all the parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
In the "Rio de Janeiro Declaration" issued at the end of the
summit, the leaders reaffirmed their opposition to all moves of
unilateral character and with extraterritorial effect.
</P>
<P>
They pledged to promote trade liberalization through bilateral
and multilateral negotiations.
</P>
<P>
They also decided to join efforts in guaranteeing the full and
timely implementation of the commitments specified in the Uruguay
Round of multilateral trade negotiations.
</P>
<P>
They underlined the importance of the World Trade Organization
(WTO) as the main forum in promoting trade liberalization and in
establishing basic rules and guidelines for international trade.
</P>
<P>
The two-day summit, the first of its kind, was attended by 47
heads of state and government from the countries in Latin America,
the Caribbean and the European Union. The next one will be held in
Spain in 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990630.0283 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Gov't to Set up 10 Holding Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
decided to establish 10 holding companies to manage 144 state
companies (BUMNs) as part of its BUMN reform program.
</P>
<P>
"In the process of forming the holding companies, there will be
some liquidations involved along with the establishment of new
companies," State Enterprises Minister Tanri Abeng said here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of a total of 159 BUMNs currently in existence, 15 are now
excluded from the program. Those excluded include giant oil
company Pertamina and certain companies under the management of
technical departments.
</P>
<P>
Tanri said the 10 holding companies would cover various sectors
namely financial service, agro-industry and consumer products
(energy, tourism, telecommunications and mass media), strategic
industries (logistics, mining, construction, building materials)
and forestry (pulp and paper and wood products).
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the holding companies is at the heart of
the second wave of BUMN reform.
</P>
<P>
The first wave focused on the restructuring, profit and
privatization of the state companies.
</P>
<P>
"The second wave of the BUMN reform aims to empower the basis
and structure of BUMNs through the formation of holding
companies," Tanri was quoted by national newspapers Wednesday as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Tanri said his office is yet to decide on which state companies
will be closed down.
</P>
<P>
"It is still under review. There is a possibility that some
BUMNs will be consolidated," he said, citing an example of the
reduction in the number of plantation companies from 14 to four
companies or from 10 insurance companies to three.
</P>
<P>
"On the contrary, it is also possible that the government will
set up scores of new BUMNs. For instance, PT Aneka Tambang will
yield five new state companies," he said, referring to the
diversified mining company.
</P>
<P>
Review of the formation of the 10 holding companies is expected
to be completed in September. This will enable establishment of
the companies to commence by the end of the year, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990630.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Latin America, EU to Promote Integral Free Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Latin American and European
Union countries committed themselves Tuesday to promoting the
integral and mutually beneficial liberalization of trade.
</P>
<P>
In their Rio de Janeiro declaration issued at the end of the
first Latin America-EU summit that was held Monday and Tuesday,
the heads of state and government expressed their conviction that
regional integration plays an important role in the promotion of
economic growth, in trade liberalization, and economic and social
development.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the relations between the two regions in the economic
field, the declaration says that trade liberalization will help
increase prosperity and combat the destabilizing effects of
volatility in the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
The document underlines the will of the participating countries
to strengthen the multilateral trading system and the economic
relations between the two regions, as well as their commitment to
open regionalism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
