<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchanges
closed Tuesday with the benchmark IPC index surging by 70.53
points, or 1.27 percent, to 5,645.07 points.
</P>
<P>
A total of 84.247 million shares worth 116.323 million U.S.
dollars were traded as against 70.669 million shares worth 137.404
million U.S. dollars traded Monday.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the local currency peso remained unchanged,
at 9.65 to one U.S. dollar for sale and 9.30 for purchase in the
main exchange houses in the Mexico City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
