<DOCNO> XIE19990630.0287 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Rice Export Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's rice export amounted to
11,400 tons in the first two months of this year, representing an
increase of 10,200 tons over the same period of 1998, according to
the latest Economic Indicators published by the country's Central
Statistical Organization.
</P>
<P>
The figure is also 10,700 tons higher than that in the same
period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The indicators also show that Myanmar's rice export was 111,700
tons in 1998, picking up again from 16,600 tons in 1997 following
three consecutive years' drop.
</P>
<P>
As part of its measures to develop agriculture, the Myanmar
government allowed private entrepreneurs to reclaim vacant,
virgin, fallow and wet lands in the country and up to now, a total
of 467,370 hectares of such lands have been reclaimed in six
divisions and states to cultivate crops to boost the country's
agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's agriculture accounts for 36 percent of the gross
domestic product and 35 percent of the export value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
