<HEADLINE> Latin America, EU to Aid Cultural Preservation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 29 (Xihnua) -- Leaders attending the Latin
American-European Union summit pledged on Tuesday to aid the
recuperation and preservation of the vast cultural reserves in the
two regions.
</P>
<P>
They made the pledge in the "Rio de Janeiro Declaration" issued
here at the end of the summit.
</P>
<P>
They said that patrimony and cultural diversity constitute a
fundamental tie for the integration of the LA and EU countries and
for a closer relationship between the peoples of different
countries.
</P>
<P>
The participating countries also reached an accord on
stimulating exchanges between educational and cultural
institutions in the two regions.
</P>
<P>
The two-day summit was aimed at intensifying political, trade,
social and cultural cooperation between the two blocs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
