<HEADLINE> Yugoslav President Outlines Priorities to Rebuild Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic said Tuesday the republic's top priorities at present
are rebuilding homeland, reforming, restoring economic and
cultural links with other countries and establishing an open and
market-oriented economic system.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic made the remarks during a meeting with senior
Yugoslav officials on national reconstruction and reforms, the
Yugoslav state news agency Tanjug reported.
</P>
<P>
He instructed the reconstruction headquarters to finish by
November the building of new homes for all those people whose
dwellings were bombed out by the NATO air strikes and restore
normal operation of all vital transportation routes.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav president praised his people for their
contribution to the defense of the country in face of the NATO
aggression.
</P>
<P>
He called on all political parties to continue to do their part
in strengthening the national unity and achieving the country's
economic and cultural development goals.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic ordered Yugoslav officials in Kosovo and diplomats to
the United Nations to work closely with U.N. organizations to
implement relevant U.N. Security Council resolutions and protect
the safety of all ethnic communities in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also discussed ways to stabilize the country's
finance and prices and promote production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
