<HEADLINE> FAO Predicts Fall in Global Cereal Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The UN Food and Agricultural
Organization (FAO) predicted Tuesday that the world-wide cereal
production will drop by 1.3 percent in 1999 from last year.
</P>
<P>
The production will amount to 1.85 billion tons in 1999, and
this quantity can not cover the expected consumption needs during
the 1999-2000 period, said FAO.
</P>
<P>
The organization foresaw a slight fall in production in Africa
and Asia and a more pronounced one in North America and Europe.
</P>
</TEXT>
