<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Clubs Can Play in European Competitions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavian club teams will be
allowed to take part in next season's major competitions in Europe,
European soccer's governing body UEFA said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
UEFA confirmed that organizational and logistical requirements
to stage international matches in Yugoslavia had been met.
</P>
<P>
The draws will be held recently for the qualifying round of the
revamped Champions' League and UEFA Cup competitions.
</P>
<P>
UEFA also said clubs from Bosnia-Herzegovina would not
participate in next season's competitions following the
cancellation of the qualifying tournament involving clubs from
that country.
</P>
<P>
Belarus champions Dnepr Transmash-Mogilev will enter the
Champions' League qualifying phase directly into the second round
instead of the first due to Bosnia-Herzegovina absence.
</P>
<P>
In the UEFA Cup, Belgium club Lierse and Slovakia side Dukla
Banska Bystrica will skip the qualifying matches and go directly
into the first round. 
