<HEADLINE> Bush Leads in Fund Raising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Texas Governor George Bush
leads in fund raising with a record of more than 20 million
dollars during the first six months of this year, his aides said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Vice President Al Gore has raised more than
18 million dollars in the first half of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The leading Republican candidate, George W. Bush, has raised
millions more than Gore, the Democratic front-runner for 2000
presidential election.
</P>
<P>
Gore will report a fund-raising total of 18.2 million dollars
to 18.5 million dollars, according to deputy campaign chairman
Marla Romash.
</P>
<P>
Gore's only Democratic rival Bill Bradley, former New Jersey
Senator, will report about 11 million dollars raised this year,
his campaign officials said.
</P>
<P>
All Presidential candidates must file their financial
disclosure statements for the second quarter of 1999 with the
Federal Election Commission by July 15.
</P>
<P>
Gore ended the first quarter as the leader in the
traditionally pivotal race for money. He had 8.9 million
dollars, followed by Bush, at 7.6 million dollars, and Bradley,
at 4.3 million dollars.  
</P>
