<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Australian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review:
</P>
<P>
-- The Australian economy now had its fifth and most important
pillar in place with the government's historic reform of the tax
system, Australian Prime Minister John Howard said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Canberra Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The Australian coalition government spent 711 million
Australian dollars (469 million U.S. dollars) to get rid of nearly
20,000 federal public servants in its first two years, Auditor
General Pat Barrett said.
</P>
<P>
