<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on Tuesday
called on the Indonesian police to investigate an incident in
which a regional office of the U.N. Mission in East Timor (UNAMET)
was attacked.
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary-General deplores in the strongest terms today's
attack on the Maliana regional office of UNAMET," a statement
issued by Annan's spokesman said. (UN-East Timor)
