</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- The Latin American, Caribbean and European
Union heads of state or of government demanded Tuesday the
establishment of a just free trade system and the strengthening of
the financial systems to prevent future economic crises.
</P>
<P>
Both stances are contained in the Declaration of Rio and in the
Joint Declaration signed by the leaders attending the first summit
of Latin America (LA), the Caribbean and the EU that started
Monday and concluded Tuesday. (LA-EU-Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- Population and development catches world
attention again when the U.N. General Assembly holds a special
session on the subject from June 30 to July 2.
</P>
<P>
With speakers from over 140 countries, the session will
highlight issues specific to global population and sustainable
development initiatives, such as the mobilization of resources,
adolescent pregnancy, maternal mortality and reproductive health.
(UN-Population-Development)
