<HEADLINE> Anelka: I Want Out of Arsenal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League soccer club
Arsenal striker Nicolas Anelka has given the clearest indication
that he wants to leave the club.
</P>
<P>
And the Frenchman will go to Lazio if his preferred move to
Real Madrid falls through. Anelka's agents have been negotiating
with Real Madrid while the Gunners have been trying to tie up a
deal with Lazio, and Anelka has now publicly stated that he sees
his future away from Highbury.
</P>
<P>
He said: "My priority is to join Real Madrid but if that does
not work out why not Lazio? I prefer that than to return to
Arsenal."
</P>
<P>
He added: "I would have no problem going to Italy. I always
planned to play there one day."
</P>
<P>
Arsenal, who have placed a 21 million pounds price tag on the
French star, have complained to FIFA that transfer rules have been
broken by the player's representatives holding talks with Real
without their permission but Anelka rejects the allegations.
</P>
<P>
"All the clubs do that. Arsenal did the same thing with me to
get me to leave Paris St Germain," Anelka told France's L'Equipe
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal boss Arsene Wenger, who is on holiday on the Riviera
after a knee operation, said: "Two weeks ago, I was sure Anelka
was going to stay but today I'm a little more pessimistic because
he is showing a real determination to leave us.
</P>
<P>
"Everything will be sorted out before the start of training on
July 13," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
