<HEADLINE> IFC Finances Fertilizer Producer in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) announced on Tuesday that it has signed an
agreement to loan 65 million U.S. dollars to Fertilizantes
Fosfatados S.A. (Fosfertil), the leading fertilizer producer in
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Fosfertil is Brazil's biggest fertilizer producer with one
third of the domestic Nitrogen and Phosphate market. The Brazilian
fertilizer market has grown at an average rate of 10 percent since
1992, while domestic production has not kept pace.
</P>
<P>
The investment will help Fosfertil to retain its market and
continue to operate as the industry's lowest cost producer, the
IFC said.
</P>
<P>
IFC's financing for the 214-million-dollar project consists of
a loan of 20 million dollars for its own account and a syndicated
loan of 45 million dollars for the account of participants.
</P>
<P>
The investment will be used to expand production of core
products, retrofit an ammonium nitrate plant, and upgrade and
expand port facilities to increase operational flexibility and
reduce freight costs.
</P>
<P>
The mission of IFC, a member of the World Bank Group, is to
promote private sector investment in developing countries, which
will reduce poverty and improve people's lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
